node.title: Car crashes through walls of Melbourne shopping centre, hitting six people
node.alt: An emergency service worker walks past the rubble of a shopping centre wall.
node.description: Four people are taken to hospital after a car crashes into the Northcote Plaza shopping centre in Melbourne's inner north.
node.content: ["Four people have been hospitalised\u00a0after a car crashed into a shopping centre in Melbourne's inner north.", "Ambulance Victoria was called to the Northcote Plaza about 10:50am.", "The car entirely breached one of the walls of the suburban shopping centre, coming to a stop inside a retail store.", "Police said a total of six pedestrians were struck by the car.", "A man and a woman were taken to the Royal Melbourne Hospital in a stable condition, Ambulance Victoria said.", "Another man was treated at the scene for upper body injuries and was later taken to the Royal Melbourne Hospital in a serious but stable condition.", "Another woman was taken to St Vincent's Hospital for observation.", "\"The driver of the vehicle, who also sustained non life-threatening injuries, is currently assisting police at the scene with their enquiries,\" a police spokesperson said.", "Police said the incident was not being treated as suspicious.", "Part of the building was evacuated for a structural assessment after the damage."]
